org.swisscheese.swisscheese.map.maze

Class CellGrid

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.swisscheese.swisscheese.map.maze.CellGrid

  • public class CellGrid
extends java.lang.Object
    The CellGrid class creates a CellGrid object necessary for the generation of the maze.

    The CellGrid is similar to a chess/checkers board (but larger), with each cell having a wall, and when generation algorithm is creating the maze, it marks the 2D boolean arrays of the wall that it is breaking as true.

    CellGrid also has a method (checkRemainingPaths()) for checking the number of paths that the algorithm can go (unvisited cells). If checkRemainingPaths returns 0, the algorithm starts to back-track.

    THE SIZE AND THE GRID MUST BE AN EVEN NUMBER, OTHERWISE IT WILL NOT WORK!

    Since:
    v0.2, 2018-11-14

      • gridTo2DArray

        public int[][] gridTo2DArray()
        Converts an the CellGrid object to an 2D int array. If a wall is to be drawn in that location, the Integer will have a value of 1, else value of 0.

        Integers are used instead of booleans because the int value represents the type of wall texture used. (randomly selected by a different method).

        Returns:
        CellGrid as a 2D int Array
